===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|Weapon}} A long-bladed [[weapon]] having a handle and sometimes a [[hilt]] and designed to stab, cut or [[slash]]. <!-- This is encyclopedic: It was sheathed in a [[scabbard]]. It was originally a [[melée]] weapon that was used in serious combat, but now is mostly used in sports and for ceremonies, and is viewed as one of the most noble weapons.-->
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1509''': [[Unsheathe]] your [[sword]] and [[dub]] him [[presently]]. &mdash; William Shakespeare, ''Henry VI'', Part III, Act II, Scene II, line 59.
#:*'''1786''': Some [[sword]]s were also made [[solely]] to [[thrust]], and some only to [[cut]]; others were [[equally]] [[adapt]]ed for both. &mdash; Francis Grose, ''A Treatise on Ancient Armour and Weapons'', page 49.
# Someone [[paid]] to [[handle]] a sword.
# A [[suit]] in the minor [[arcana]] in [[tarot]].
# A [[card]] of this suit.

